      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:3:99:5",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ الْمُحْرِمِ يَتَخَلَّلُ قَالَ لَا بَأْسَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, and Ahmad Bin Idrees, from Muhammad Bin Ahmad, from Ahmad Bin Al Hassan, from Amro Bin Saeed, from Musaddaq Bin Sadawa, from Ammar Bin Musa, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I asked him<sup>asws</sup> about the one in <span class=\"iTxt\">Ihraam</span>, whether he can pick (clean) his teeth’. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There is no problem’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "5. Muhammad ibn Yahya and Ahmad ibn Idris has narrated from Muhammad ibn Ahmad from Ahmad ibn al-Hassan from ’Amr ibn Sa‘id from Musaddiq ibn Sadaqah from ‘Ammar ibn Musa who has said the following: “I once asked abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about a man who uses a toothpick while he is in the state of Ihram. He (the Imam) said, ‘It is not harmful.’” "
        ]
      }
